          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1626683347960-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>curry powder</strong>,<strong> cumin seeds</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>,<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and a generous amount of <strong>black pepper</strong> to the<strong> </strong>softened onion (add a little more oil if it's looking a little dry) and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>figgy coconut stock</strong>, <strong>roasted aubergine </strong>and <strong>drained chickpeas</strong>, increase the heat to medium-high and cook, covered, for 3-4 min or until the sauce has thickened slightly – this is your <strong>figgy</strong> <strong>aubergine curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1626683353584-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1626683353584-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1626683353584-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1626683353584-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
